    "content" : "I decided that I didn't want to cut away any metal, so I shortened the mount, re-drilled it, ground the back flat and fitted it as shown with a reinforcing plate behind, inside the chassis channel. I discussed it with Dave Palmer and he thought it would be fine - and it is. The top bolt goes right through, ie. two bolts through the chassis.\n<br> \n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s346.photobucket.com/user/DelBoy44/media/Rear%20shock%20mounts/file.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i346.photobucket.com/albums/p432/DelBoy44/Rear%20shock%20mounts/file.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s346.photobucket.com/user/DelBoy44/media/Rear%20shock%20mounts/file-2.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i346.photobucket.com/albums/p432/DelBoy44/Rear%20shock%20mounts/file-2.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>",
    "lastEdited" : "Thu Jul 31, 2014 7:24 pm"
